        <div id="faq" class="faq-area are_sections_faq py-120 caaft-ar-faq-wrap" aria-labelledby="ac-faq-heading"><div class="container"><div class="row"><div class="col-lg-12"><div class="faq-right wow fadeInUp"><div class="site-heading text-center mb-3"><h2 id="ac-faq-heading" class="site-title my-3">Frequently Asked Questions:</h2></div></div></div><div class="frequent-question col-lg-10"><div class="accordion wow fadeInRight" id="accordionAdvisoryFaq">
            <div class="accordion-item"><p class="accordion-header" id="acFaqHeading1"><button class="accordion-button" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#acFaqCollapse1" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="acFaqCollapse1">01. What is the difference between a virtual CFO and a regular accountant?</button></p><div id="acFaqCollapse1" class="accordion-collapse collapse show" aria-labelledby="acFaqHeading1" data-bs-parent="#accordionAdvisoryFaq"><div class="accordion-body">An accountant records and reports what has happened. A virtual CFO uses those records to advise on what should happen next - managing cash flow, building financial models, advising on funding strategy, reviewing contracts, and sitting in on board or investor conversations.</div></div></div>
            <div class="accordion-item"><p class="accordion-header" id="acFaqHeading2"><button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#acFaqCollapse2" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="acFaqCollapse2">02. At what stage of business does a virtual CFO engagement make sense?</button></p><div id="acFaqCollapse2" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="acFaqHeading2" data-bs-parent="#accordionAdvisoryFaq"><div class="accordion-body">Typically when your business is growing fast, raising funds, managing multiple revenue streams, or facing decisions with significant financial consequences.</div></div></div>
